<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-02-04T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-02-04T18:00:00-05:00" n="755" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6263: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gade</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-02-04T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            4, 1920—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your 81 [<hi rend="italic">82</hi>], January 29, 5 p.m. You may
                                informally bring to the attention of the Latvian Minister for
                                Foreign Affairs that the United States cannot give assurance of such
                                economic and military assistance as would be implied by its advising
                                the Latvian authorities to refuse to conclude an armistice with
                                Bolshevist Russia.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>